		<hr size="1">I have two main characters, one is a tailor, the other isn't but has a nice collection of swatches collected while hunting mammoth calves in Everfrost.  They live too far apart to trade between them, and the one in Everfrost isn't a tailor, so i've been selling them at 5gp each.  I'm never too short on cash because tailors are so used to paying 1pp each (outrageous, yes), they snatch my swatchs up so fast i have to take back orders.  </P><P>On the other hand, i see people shouting that they are selling swatches for 1pp each, or 15pp for a stack (oh what a bargain *rolls eyes*)...and they auction, and shout, and ooc, and auction, shout, ooc, and it goes on so long that i wonder if they ever do sell them.  </P><P>So basically, even though my character is selling the swatches and therefore i should be asking as much money as i can get, i have been making a small difference in one area in lowering the price.  I mean, what good is plat gonna be when it ends up costing so much to buy simple little things?  If it keeps up the way it has been, a plat when our "fresh new server" opened is going to be worth only a gold piece, it's gonna take so many to buy anything.  The trade skills become worthless, as the npc vendors sell things cheaper than players, eventually our economy is down the bushes (Norrath doesn't have toilets).<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
