		<hr size="1">Ever tried haggling with someone?  It's a good way to guarantee you won't make the sale/buy.</P><P>It might just be the areas i've been in.  If someone is selling something for x pp, and someone offers a little less than x, it seems to piss the seller off.  On the other hand, if someone wants to buy something, and you offer to sell it at a price a little higher than they want to pay, that pisses them off too.</P><P>The problem is that people are too greedy.  Last night, i was hanging out in everfrost collecting spider silks because i have just started tailoring, and there's no way i'm gonna pay 1pp per silk/swatch.  Some guy auctioned some banded armor, which gets harder to sell every day.  Fewer and fewer people are willing to buy that these days because the market is gettting saturated.  This guy tried to sell his banded for 2pp per ac.  Several people tried to nicely tell him that the standard price is 1pp per ac for banded, 2pp per ac is for bronze.  The guy said that if we knew how much it cost him to make this stuff, we wouldn't be complaining.  That's when the other smiths jumped in and said that 1pp per ac is profit enough, and since it's the standard rate, nobody will pay 2pp.  <BR>The guy apparently just didn't get it.  Or maybe he was new to that level of smithing and doesn't know that the market in that area is saturated full, and in a saturated market, the only way to sell your wares is to bring the price DOWN, not up.  Finally someone else started selling at the normal price, and the guy quieted down.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
