		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=178&FN=Zebuxoruk&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=892477&TN=Zebuxoruk+Economy&CAT=Servers&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1298443&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1">I've seen full suits of banded auctioned for as low as 70pp in EC recently but more often the 'standard' price of 1pp/ac is applied.  Since your cost (assuming no failures) to make it is approximately 51pp there is still room for small profit at the lower price but really you're just looking to make enough to finance more skillups at this point.  It doesn't get much better once you start on fine plate.  Too many smiths are using the 10pp/ac rule, or buyers are expecting this, and in either case it makes it hard for those using the 75pp/sheet pricing model to sell.  At 10pp/ac there is little room for failure.  I've taken to only selling in-stock items in order to reduce the risk that I'll run out of supplies or plat before finishing an order.  </P><P>The earlier comment on haggling still holds true.  I set an asking price which is what I want for an item, but am willing to bargain some.  I also offer less than the asking price when buying, assuming that others work along the same principles.  That's all part of an active economy.  The problem I encounter is that people expect me to sell my stuff on the cheap yet want me to pay the highest price they found on Allak'hazam or EQPrices for their goods.  No problem as long as we both see the initial offer or asking price as a starting point and work from there, but some folks get right annoyed when you try to chop a few plat off a hideously inflated asking price.  They can sometimes get equally indignant at my asking price and respond with a rude comment, thus ending yet another promising bargaining session.  If you don't like my asking price feel free to make a counter-offer, and we will work from there.  </P><P>Fyorkin Fornax<BR>33rd level Disciple of Brell<BR>Lone Wolves of Norrath, Zebuxoruk<BR>Master Smith<BR>Master Potter<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
