		<font size="2" face="Verdana">
		<font size="1" face="Verdana">posted 3/5/2002 7:53:25 PM&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;

		
		<a href="MB_editmsg.asp?FID=178&FN=Zebuxoruk&SID=7&SN=EverQuest&TID=892477&TN=Zebuxoruk+Economy&CAT=Servers&SURL=http%3A%2F%2Fwww%2Eeverlore%2Ecom&MSID=1392521&PL=4">
		<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/edit.gif" border="0" alt="Edit/Delete Message" width="18" height="13"></a>
		
		</font>
		<hr size="1"> Just a general comment on Zeb's economy.<BR>I began as a newbie on the Zeb server, and have been playing for well over a year now. I fully understand the frustration of the lower level toons as they struggle to to afford adequate gear. Believe me, I lived from drop to drop, and was perpetually broke, until I was close to level 50 and really started to collect some decent scores. No, it's not easy. The best advice I can give is loot everything that you're entitled to (but DON'T be a ninja-looter when grouping - a bad reputaion will be your undoing), know the going rate for any given item whether it be the typical selling price or buying price (there is a variance, and it will change over a given period of time), learn how to haggle, excersize extreme patience when auctioning (refrain from buying too high or selling too low just because you're getting tired of auctioning), and recognize a good deal when they come along.<BR> Some may find it surprising, but the economy on Zeb is grossly undervalued when it comes to many of the more common items. That Lammy that you see being auctioned for the appalling price of 3k is actually insanely inexpensive for such a nice piece of equipment as you'll find they typically sell for 7k+ on just about any other server... and the same follows suit for a great many items on Zeb. What it basically comes down to is that Zeb is a great server to buy on, but sux for the sellers.<BR> Some items, on the other hand simply don't follow suit. Crafted gear, and crafting supplies tend to fall into this category. Banded armor has been 1pp per AC since the day I started, and it hasn't changed. And you'll still pay 5k for a velium/bd bracer. I do agree that some of the asking prices you'll get are unreasonable. As I'm now bringing up tailoring with my cleric, I'm simply not going to be led to believe that 10p is the going rate for a stack of spiderling, yes spider-ling, silks. I know better. But again, if you know what the typical price is, you have to be willing to stick to your guns. I offer 2p per stack for spiderling silks (maybe 3p to a regular customer), and 10p per stack of spider silks - that's what I'm willing to pay, take it or leave it. I have no intention of harrassing you about your prices, plz afford me the same courtesy. If you know someone who will pay you 20p for the same stack, more power to you.<BR> At any rate, thus is the world we live in... on Zeb anyways. Try to make the most of it. Sure I hate to let such a sweet weap as a Centi longsword go for 1500p, but then I have to remember that I was able buy a liz-scale cloak for 200p, way back when. And to those of you who may be saying 'For the love of all that is sacred! When will I EVER be able to afford that kind of money?!'... in due time. You may be surprised.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
	</td>
</tr>
