		<hr size="1">/agree</P><P>I totally hear what you're saying Fellik about not having the cash for purchases.  I am a totally untwinked Druid.  I purchased/looted absolutely everything that I own.  I would say that I am doing pretty well too (203 wis and about 45 mana at level 40).  I've made some money, but as soon as I had it I would upgrade to a piece of gear that was a little better than what I owned.  That has constantly made me poor.  It has only been in the past level or 3 that I've had what I would call decent money.  I have about 2500pp to my name(not much to many, but a lot to me), and I expect that to go down before too long since I am still looking for upgrades.  For the longest time I only had a couple hundred pp to my name at most.  Just stick with what you're doing and the money will come.  It will come slowly, but it will come.</P><P>Gaiah Enapkallu<BR>Druid of Tunare<BR>Guildleader<BR>Tunare's Benevolence<BR>Zebuxoruk Server<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
